{
  "texts": [
    "ADQN-FBDD generates more druglike compounds because it considers chemical reaction laws and the three-dimensional shape of the binding site.",
    "As a result, ADQN-FBDD can effectively probe the chemical space around the given target.",
    "The capacity of RL-based models to perform distributed computations is their greatest strength since this drastically shortens training times in many scenarios.",
    "When several computers are deployed, even the vast chemical space may be investigated efficiently (Horgan et al., 2018).",
    "However, the quality of the representation of the training data might significantly impact the performance of the models mentioned above."
  ]
}